<http://datadock.io/kal/local_data_1/id/resource/monument_record_no/108M> <http://datadock.io/kal/local_data_1/id/definition/monument_desc> "House with ground-floor shop. Nos.1 & 1a Chirstmas Steps. Largely of 1747 or early 1748. No.1, on the corner of Host Street, was the baker's house, with a shop occupying part of the ground floor. It was of three and a half storeys plus a small cellar. Three bays faced Host Street and one faced Christmas Steps. Incorporated at the southern end was an earlier dwelling of three storeys and ridge roof, one bay in width. To the west on the Steps lay No.1a, containing the bakery and oven on the ground floor, and three storeys of storage above. A small lock-up shop was later installed at the front of the property. The party wall between Nos.1a and 2 was partly medieval and included the remains of two arches."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> <http://datadock.io/kal/local_data_1/id/dataset/Bristol_Monuments.csv>.
